parametrization of differential rotation in stars with convective
envelopes in circular orbits to predict the difference between the
surface rotation period and the orbital period. Comparing this
parametrization to observed eclipsing binary systems, we find that in
the surface convection zones of stars in short-period binaries there is
very little radial differential rotation, with |r{$\partial$}rln
{$\Omega$}| {$<$} 0.02. This holds even for longer orbital periods, though
it is harder to say which systems are synchronized at long periods, and
larger differential rotation is degenerate with asynchronous rotation.},
